  <span id="freeText12894776870149770336" style="display:none">Wangari Maathai is an incredible human being - everyone should know her name and all that she has accomplished with regards to environmentalism, peace, feminism, and democracy in Kenya and around the world. That being said, the book was often quite dry, and for a good 1/3 it read more like a Kenya history textbook than a memoir. Still, I'm glad I read it and know more about this amazing woman.</span>
